TITLE: Jill Biden declares her love for Hunter Biden amid GOP probe: 'I'll support him any way I can'
SUMMARY: First Lady Jill Biden said she will support Hunter Biden "any way I can" as he is investigated by GOP lawmakers for his allegedly corrupt business dealings.

TITLE: Manhunt in Georgia for ‘dangerous’ inmate who left work detail, authorities say
SUMMARY: Authorities in Georgia are searching for William Knight, an inmate serving time for involuntary manslaughter, after he left a work detail on Monday, officials said.

TITLE: NFL star Derek Carr has brilliant punishment for XFL players involved in melee
SUMMARY: XFL players were involved in a skirmish on Sunday during a game between the Defenders and BattleHawks and NFL star Derek Carr had the best way to punish them.

TITLE: China, US heading for 'conflict and confrontation,' foreign minister warns
SUMMARY: Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs Qin Gang accused the United States of pushing Taiwan to the brink of destruction by interfering with Chinese claims of sovereignty over the island.

TITLE: Norfolk Southern train collides with dump truck in Cleveland, Ohio, killing conductor
SUMMARY: A Norfolk Southern employee was reportedly killed Tuesday morning when a train crashed into a dump truck while passing through a Cleveland-Cliffs Cleveland Works property.

TITLE: Missing lawyer Ciera Breland's mom believes she was killed
SUMMARY: The mother of Ciera Breland, a lawyer and mother from Indiana who disappeared in February 2022, says her family believes she was killed and hopes her body will be found.

TITLE: Josh Hawley unveils bill to stop Chinese corporations, CCP-linked entities from buying US farmland
SUMMARY: Missouri Sen. Josh Hawley told Fox News Digital that "no Chinese corporation or individual associated with the CCP should be permitted to own American farmland."

TITLE: Here's how Cadillac's semi-autonomous Celestiq will work
SUMMARY: The Cadillac Celestiq electric luxury car will have over 20 sensors including lidar that will enable its Ultra Cruise system to drive it 95% of the time.

TITLE: Closing statements set Tuesday in OH corruption trial of former house speaker, lobbyist
SUMMARY: Closing statements are set Tuesday in an Ohio corruption trial where two Republicans are charged with conspiracy to participate in a racketeering enterprise.

TITLE: SUV smashes into Houston coffee shop, hits two men during live podcast: video
SUMMARY: Two men in Texas were minding their own business, creating content at a coffee shop when an SUV came barreling right at them. The two walked away with minor injuries.

TITLE: NYPD video shows wanted suspects caught on camera defacing more than a century-old Christopher Columbus statue
SUMMARY: The NYPD released video showing two suspects accused of tagging "Murderer" and "Give Us Our Land Back" on a statue of Christopher Columbus commissioned in 1892 in Central Park.

TITLE: Treasury Department accused of blocking GOP lawmakers' access to 'suspicious' Biden family bank transactions
SUMMARY: Rep. James Comer, R-Ky., joined 'Fox & Friends First' to discuss the FBI investigating a kidnapping of four Americans in Mexico and a Treasury official who is set to testify in the Biden family probe.

TITLE: Southern California residents frustrated after record snowfall traps them for over a week: 'Exhausting'
SUMMARY: While southern California officials are working to clear roads and provide food and emergency services after record snowfall, some residents are frustrated with the response.

TITLE: COVID-19 shocker: Parents lied about their kids’ sickness status and broke quarantine rules, study finds
SUMMARY: A study published in the Jama Network Open found that nearly 26% of parents lied about their kids' COVID-19 status in order to preserve personal freedoms and prevent kids from missing school.

TITLE: Biden admin weighs revival of policy to detain migrant families amid southern border crisis: reports
SUMMARY: The Biden administration is reportedly considering the revival of a policy that would detain migrant families who cross the southern border illegally.

TITLE: Celtics forward Grant Williams' trash talk epically fails as he misses clutch free throws in Boston's loss
SUMMARY: Boston Celtics forward Grant Williams told Cleveland Cavaliers star Donovan Mitchell he would sink two clutch free throws to win the game Monday night but missed them both.

TITLE: Supreme Court denies petition from Florida city to toss atheists' First Amendment suit over prayer vigil
SUMMARY: The U.S. Supreme Court on Monday handed atheists a temporary win by rejecting a the City of Ocala, Florida's request to toss a lawsuit over a prayer vigil.

TITLE: California Gov. Newsom took 'personal trip' to Baja California during devastating winter storms
SUMMARY: California Gov. Gavin Newsom, who faced criticism for leaving the state last week during record-breaking winter storms, has returned from Baja California, Mexico, his office says.

TITLE: 'History of the World, Part II' will be 'offensive,' 'push the envelope,' cast members claim
SUMMARY: Cast members and directors of the sequel to the Mel Brooks classic 'History of the World' told E! News in recent interviews that the sequel series will be 'offensive.'

TITLE: OK residents to vote on legalizing recreational marijuana Tuesday
SUMMARY: Oklahoma voters will decide whether the state should legalize recreational marijuana Tuesday. If approved, those over 21 years old would be able to use it.

TITLE: UK school blasted for replacing girls' bathroom mirrors with 'provocative' posters: 'Very medieval'
SUMMARY: England's Christopher Whitehead Language College came under fire from parents for replacing bathroom mirrors with posters featuring controversial messages about makeup.

TITLE: Human bone found at Milwaukee beach
SUMMARY: A human bone was discovered at Milwaukee beach, Wisconsin, by a person walking along the shore. Other remains were found too but may belong to an animal.

TITLE: Lena Dunham denies using N-word after Donald Glover joke: 'Never used, nor would use'
SUMMARY: A representative for Lena Dunham said in a statement Monday that she never used the N-word after Donald Glover said otherwise during the WGA Awards.

TITLE: MLB should boycott Florida under DeSantis, columnist claims: ‘Baseball can no longer ignore' culture wars
SUMMARY: Washington Post columnist Kevin B. Blackistone argued Major League Baseball should consider moving its training operations out of Florida to punish Ron DeSantis.

TITLE: Sister of Bengals star Joe Mixon denies running back was involved in incident that left juvenile injured
SUMMARY: Cincinnati Bengals running back Joe Mixon's sister denied her brother was involved in an incident in which a juvenile was left injured.
